# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_elder_week1 (Elder, intro scout quest) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week1.root.body=I'm Lyren. I speak for the charter we signed when we put this town on Orbis. The old cities are gone. What we have is this ground and the people who are already here, and more will come. Before we start laying new plots, I need you to learn the land around Aetherhaven: where it is flat enough to build, where water runs, where we might put fields or a commons later. Keep it practical. When you have looked the place over, come find me again.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week1.root.c0=I'll scout the area and report back.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week1.root.speaker=Elder Lyren
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_elder_week2 (Elder, inn / hall / house & gold) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.gold_explainer.body=You pick some up from the work we send you on, and from trading when someone is buying. The town purse is its own thing. Once the hall is built, the treasury lives in there. Use the block there to put coin in or pull it out if the charter says you may. After that, each morning a little gold flows into that treasury from the people who actually live here, not visitors passing through. How much depends on how they are holding up. If they are fed, rested, and in decent spirits, the pot does better. If they are stretched thin, it does worse. That keeps the commons honest.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.gold_explainer.c0=Good to know. Thanks.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.gold_explainer.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.inn_done.body=There. A real inn for people who would otherwise sleep rough. Corin has the key. Go introduce yourself by the hearth. You earned more than thanks, but thanks is where I will start.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.inn_done.c0=Happy to help.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.inn_done.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_accepted.body=When the walls are up, use the management block and set me as resident. Then come find me. I want to hear you say it, not read it off a shelf.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_accepted.c0=You will get both.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_accepted.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_finish.body=Then it is settled. I have a home under the same rules as everyone else. Thank you for seeing it through.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_finish.c0=Welcome home, Lyren.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_finish.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_offer.body=The hall is up and the treasury can breathe. The charter gave us rules for the town; it did not give me a bed. I want the same small house anyone else gets. Take the token I offer, stake the plot with your staff, pay materials and the town share from the treasury, then put my name on the management shelf when it is built. I will not forget who made room for me.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_offer.c0=I'll handle it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_offer.c1=I cannot commit to that yet.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_offer.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_remind.body=Take the time you need. When the house is done, register me on the block, then come find me so we can finish this face to face.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_remind.c0=I'll come when it is done.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.lyren_house_remind.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.quest_accepted.body=Good. Place the inn plot with your staff, pay the materials the sign lists, and finish the build. When the roof is on and the hearth is in, come tell me yourself. I will be waiting on word.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.quest_accepted.c0=I'll start as soon as I can.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.quest_accepted.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.remind_inn.body=When the roof holds and the hearth is lit, come back and tell me in person. I am not rushing you, but I am not leaving until this town has a proper inn for anyone who needs a bed.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.remind_inn.c0=I'll come back when it is ready.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.remind_inn.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.rep_reward_100.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.rep_reward_50.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.body=The charter still stands, and I still stand by it. We do not have spare shelter to send people to, so the first real building here has to be an inn: a roof, a hearth, and a door that stays open to travelers and to our own kin when the road is long. When you are ready to stake it, say so.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c0=I'm in. Let's raise the inn.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c1=The inn is still on my list. I wanted to check in.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c10=I'll leave you to it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c2=The inn is finished. Corin should have what he needs.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c3=About the town hall.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c4=I put your name on the shelf. You should hear it from me first.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c5=Your house is not done yet, but I am on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c6=You mentioned wanting a house of your own.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c7=The town hall build is still underway.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c8=The town hall is up.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.c9=How do people get gold coins around here?
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.root.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_accepted.body=Use the town hall token with your staff, pay the materials, and build it out. When the hall is finished, tell me in person. I want to see your face when you say it is done.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_accepted.c0=I'll tell you the moment it is finished.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_accepted.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_done.body=There. Aetherhaven has a proper town hall: records, treasury, and a room where we can meet without yelling across the square. That is what I needed from you.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_done.c0=Glad it helps.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_done.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_offer.body=The inn is standing. Next we need a town hall that belongs to all of us: a shelf for the charter, a desk for plans, and a treasury so shared coin can fund the rest of what we build. Stake the plot, pay what the sign asks in materials, and we finally have a place to meet as a whole town.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_offer.c0=I'll put the hall up.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_offer.c1=Not yet.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_offer.speaker=Elder Lyren
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_remind.body=Stone and paperwork both take time. When the hall is finished, tell me. I will be here.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_remind.c0=Still working on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_elder_week2.town_hall_remind.speaker=Elder Lyren
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_farmer (Irienne Mossmark) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_abandoned.body=All right. If you still want rows here, say so.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_abandoned.c0=Will do.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_abandoned.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_accepted.body=I will stay at the inn until the soil stops pretending it is floorboards. Then find me behind the bench with mud on my boots.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_accepted.c0=See you there.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_accepted.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_building.body=When the plot is built, I will walk over to the farming bench and set up. Come find me there and we will call it done.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_building.c0=I need to drop the quest.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_building.c1=I will keep going.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_building.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_done.body=That plot will feed more than complaints. I will keep the beds turning while the town grows.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_done.c0=Grow well.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_done.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_accepted.body=When the roof holds, register me on the block, then find me. I want to end this with both feet on my own floorboards.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_accepted.c0=Count on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_accepted.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_finish.body=Roots under my own rafters. That is the crop I wanted.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_finish.c0=Glad to hear it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_finish.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_offer.body=The fields are honest work. I still want a door that is not the inn's. Same token as anyone. Build it, then list me on the shelf.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_offer.c0=I'll build it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_offer.c1=Not yet.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_offer.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_remind.body=Wood and weather take their time. When the house is done, assign me, then come tell me the rest.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_remind.c0=I'll find you.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_house_remind.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_quest_farm.body=I have been counting cracks in Corin's floorboards and dreaming of rows with my name on them. Stake a farm plot, fence it, set the bench. Craft the plot token at your planning desk, place it with your staff, pay the sign. I will meet you at the farming bench when the ground is ready.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_quest_farm.c0=We'll get it built.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_quest_farm.c1=Not right now.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.irienne_quest_farm.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.rep_reward_100.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.rep_reward_25.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.rep_reward_50.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.rep_reward_75.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.body=Irienne Mossmark. Dirt does not care who owned it yesterday. It cares what you feed it tomorrow. I slept enough nights on Corin's floor to know a warm bowl beats pride.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c0=You wanted to talk about your own place.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c1=Your name is on the shelf. Figured you'd want to hear it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c2=Your house is still rising.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c3=Good to see the farm feeding you.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c4=The farm is ready when you are.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c5=About the fields...
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c6=You said you could use a farmer in town.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.c7=Get some rest.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_farmer.root.speaker=Irienne Mossmark
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_inn_welcome (Corin Mosscup) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_accepted.body=Then I will keep the kettle here until the plot is yours. Once my name is on the shelf, come find me. I want to shake your hand before we call it settled.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_accepted.c0=Count on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_accepted.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_finish.body=There. A hearth for strangers and a latch that belongs to me. That is worth more than the key looks.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_finish.c0=You earned it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_finish.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_offer.body=I will pour soup for the whole town, but I would like a door that closes on my own mess. Same house token as anyone else. Build it, list me on the block when it stands.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_offer.c0=I'll get it built.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_offer.c1=Another time.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_offer.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_remind.body=Clay dries at its own pace. When the house is done, assign me on the shelf and come tell me so we can close the book on this.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_remind.c0=I'll let you know.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.corin_house_remind.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.inn_explain_pool.body=We keep two spots for folk passing through. Traders, tinkers, anyone the town can stand behind. Turn them away and most nights they sleep under sky. That is not pride. That is math.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.inn_explain_pool.c0=Makes sense.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.inn_explain_pool.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.rep_reward_100.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.rep_reward_50.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.rep_reward_75.speaker=Corin Mosscup
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.body=Step in out of the wind. I'm Corin. I keep this hearth, and while you are under our roof you are fed as well as we can manage. That still matters, even when the world outside forgets how.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.c0=How do guest beds work?
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.c1=You wanted a real room of your own.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.c2=I listed you on the house shelf. Thought you should hear it from me.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.c3=Your house is still coming together. I am on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.c4=I'll go stir the pot.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_inn_welcome.root.speaker=Corin Mosscup
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_merchant (Vex Sunderlane) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.rep_reward_100.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.rep_reward_50.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.body=Vex Sunderlane. I buy salvage, sell hope, and count coins twice. Your inn with a working hearth is already the best shop front for miles. Everything else is negotiation.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c0=Browse your wares (gold coins).
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c2=You mentioned wanting a house.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c3=I put you on the ledger. Paper should match reality.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c4=Your house is still on the pile.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c5=Good to see you trading here.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c6=The stall is up. Come see.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c7=About the stall build...
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c8=You asked me to find space for a stall.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.c9=Keep your purse closed in the wind.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.root.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_abandoned.body=Fair. If you change your mind, the offer stays.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_abandoned.c0=Thanks.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_abandoned.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_accepted.body=I will camp at Corin's until the stall is standing. Safer than a ditch, and the soup is better.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_accepted.c0=See you when it is up.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_accepted.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_building.body=When the stall is built, I will head over and open shop. Come find me there and we will wrap this up.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_building.c0=I need to drop the quest.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_building.c1=I will keep working on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_building.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_done.body=Stall looks honest. Trade will be thin at first. We grow it the slow way, same as everything worth keeping.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_done.c0=Here's to that.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_done.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_accepted.body=When the door swings, put my name on the block, then find me. I want the story, not just the ink.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_accepted.c0=You will get both.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_accepted.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_finish.body=There. A door that knows my knock. That beats a full strongbox.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_finish.c0=Enjoy it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_finish.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_offer.body=Stock belongs on shelves. My boots belong somewhere dry. Same house token as the rest of town. Register me when it is built.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_offer.c0=I'll stake a house.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_offer.c1=Another time.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_offer.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_remind.body=Houses take seasons sometimes. Finish it, assign me, then come back and we will balance the ledger.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_remind.c0=I'll come back.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_house_remind.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_quest_stall.body=I need a little roof and a counter I can lean on. You place it with your staff while you hold the token I hand you. Materials are your problem. I will run the counter when the nails hold.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_quest_stall.c0=I'll build it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_quest_stall.c1=Not right now.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_merchant.vex_quest_stall.speaker=Vex Sunderlane
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_priestess (Serah Thornwell) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.body=Serah Thornwell. I lead Gaia's rites for this town. The inn is a roof over my head, and I am grateful, but I cannot run services wedged between supper and card games. I need a real altar outside: paths, a few stools, and the statue where people can pray without holding their breath from the kitchen smoke.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c0=You wanted to speak about a home.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c1=You're on the shelf now. I thought you should know.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c2=The house is still unfinished.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c3=How is the altar working out for you?
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c4=The altar grounds are ready.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c5=About the blessing...
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c6=You said you needed ground for Gaia.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.c7=I'll leave you to it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.root.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_abandoned.body=No hard feelings. If you still want an altar in town, ask again.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_abandoned.c0=All right.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_abandoned.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_altar_accepted.body=I will stay at the inn until the altar is built. Then find me at the statue and we will finish the blessing.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_altar_accepted.c0=I'll see you there.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_altar_accepted.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_building.body=When the altar stands, I will walk to the statue. Come find me there and we will call it done.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_building.c0=I need to drop the quest.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_building.c1=I'm still working on it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_building.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_done.body=The altar is finished. Thank you. I will keep the grounds tended and hold rites here as the town grows.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_done.c0=Good luck with it.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_done.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_accepted.body=When the house is up, put my name on the management block inside, then come find me. I want to hear you say it in person, not just read it off a list.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_accepted.c0=You will.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_accepted.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_finish.body=Good. A roof that is actually mine.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_finish.c0=Fair enough.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_finish.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_offer.body=The altar is for everyone. I still want a small house of my own, same as anyone else, so I am not living out of the inn hall forever. Build it from the usual token, then register me on the management block when it is up.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_offer.c0=I'll stake a house.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_offer.c1=Another time.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_offer.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_remind.body=These things take time. When the house is done, register me on the block, then come talk. That is when we are finished.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_remind.c0=I'll come back.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_house_remind.speaker=Serah Thornwell
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_quest_altar.body=Stake a Gaia altar plot: paths, stools, and the statue where I can stand and folk can sit. Craft the token at your planning desk, place it with your staff, and pay the sign. When it is built, meet me at the statue and we will bless it properly.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_quest_altar.c0=We'll get it built.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_quest_altar.c1=Not right now.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_priestess.serah_quest_altar.speaker=Serah Thornwell
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_visitor_elder (visitors) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_elder.root.body=You are welcome to pass through, but this charter is not yours. If you mean to help, you must be welcomed in by those who dwell here first.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_elder.root.c0=I understand.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_elder.root.speaker=Elder Lyren
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_visitor_generic (visitors) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_generic.root.body=Good day, traveler. If you are not of this settlement, speak with the locals who belong here. My hands are full with our own work.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_generic.root.c0=Farewell.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_generic.root.speaker=Villager
# -- Tree id: aetherhaven_visitor_inn (visitors) --
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_inn.root.body=The hearth is warm, but the ledger is for townsfolk and their guests. Come back when you are invited.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_inn.root.c0=Fair enough.
aetherhaven.dialogue.aetherhaven_visitor_inn.root.speaker=Innkeeper

